The paper deals with Multi-Domain Learning (MDL) and focuses on obtaining domain-specific models with an adjustable budget in terms of the number of network parameters and computational complexity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel strategy to automatically adjust the computational complexity of the network, which indicates that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) categories. Finally, the paper deals with image recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
